{"word":"σπέρμα","slug":"σπέρμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σπέρμα</b></el> <el>(σπέρμα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σπείρω'><el>σπείρω</el></a>\n<p/><i>that which is sown</i>: <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the seed</i> of plants, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:—also of animals, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of <i>the germ, origin, element</i> of anything, <el>σπ. πυρός</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>φλογός</el> <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <el>κακῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>seed, offspring, issue</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>race, origin, descent</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}